-- Project Management
('deliverable', 'A tangible or intangible good or service produced as a result of a project', 'Project Management', 'The main deliverable for this sprint is the user authentication module.', 'B1'),
('milestone', 'A significant point or event in a project timeline', 'Project Management', 'We hit our Q2 milestone ahead of schedule, which impressed the stakeholders.', 'B1'),
('scope creep', 'The uncontrolled expansion of a project''s scope without adjustments to time, cost, or resources', 'Project Management', 'We need to address the scope creep before it impacts our delivery date.', 'B2'),
('stakeholder', 'A person or group with an interest or concern in a project or business', 'Project Management', 'All stakeholders have been notified about the system downtime scheduled for Saturday.', 'B1'),
('bandwidth', 'The capacity or availability of a person or team to take on work', 'Project Management', 'I don''t have the bandwidth to take on another project this sprint.', 'B2'),
('blockers', 'Issues or obstacles that prevent a team member from progressing with their work', 'Project Management', 'Please flag any blockers in today''s standup so we can resolve them quickly.', 'B1'),
('sprint', 'A fixed time period during which a team completes a set amount of work', 'Project Management', 'We''re planning to ship the API integration in the next sprint.', 'B1'),
('retrospective', 'A meeting held at the end of a sprint to reflect on what went well and what can be improved', 'Project Management', 'During the retrospective, the team agreed to improve our code review process.', 'B2'),

-- Technical Communication
('workaround', 'A temporary solution to a problem when a proper fix is not yet available', 'Technical Communication', 'As a workaround, users can clear their cache to resolve the login issue.', 'B1'),
('bottleneck', 'A point of congestion in a system that slows down overall performance', 'Technical Communication', 'The database query is the bottleneck — it''s causing the entire page to load slowly.', 'B2'),
('deprecate', 'To declare that a feature or function is obsolete and should no longer be used', 'Technical Communication', 'We will deprecate the v1 API endpoints at the end of Q3.', 'B2'),
('refactor', 'To restructure existing code without changing its external behavior', 'Technical Communication', 'We need to refactor the authentication service before adding new features.', 'B1'),
('scalability', 'The ability of a system to handle increased workload by adding resources', 'Technical Communication', 'The new microservices architecture improves the scalability of our platform.', 'B2'),
('latency', 'The delay before a transfer of data begins following an instruction', 'Technical Communication', 'High latency in the API is causing a poor user experience for international clients.', 'B2'),
('integration', 'The process of combining software components or systems to work together', 'Technical Communication', 'The Stripe payment integration is scheduled for release next week.', 'B1'),
('rollback', 'To revert a system to a previous state, usually after a failed update', 'Technical Communication', 'We had to rollback the deployment after discovering a critical bug in production.', 'B1'),

-- Meeting & Email Phrases
('circle back', 'To return to a topic or person at a later time', 'Meeting & Email Phrases', 'Let''s circle back on the infrastructure costs after we get the vendor quotes.', 'B1'),
('take offline', 'To discuss something privately or outside the current meeting', 'Meeting & Email Phrases', 'This is getting too detailed — let''s take it offline and sync up separately.', 'B2'),
